      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Many legal experts argue that traditional antitrust laws, designed for brick-and-mortar industries, are ill-equipped for the fast-moving, network-based nature of the digital economy. Critics suggest the focus on consumer price is too narrow for tech, where harm can manifest as reduced privacy or stifled innovation. Therefore, there is a growing movement pushing for updated legislation that specifically addresses data dominance and platform gatekeeping.",
      "source": "target",
